Comments: This is a meta-project to include all sequencing done by the UW Virology NGS group. We are interested in discovering viruses and new organisms through metagenomics across Washington state, the Pacific Northwest, and the world. We are also interested in whole genome sequencing of clinical isolates to better understand transmission and resistance of microbial organisms in humans. If interested in submitting samples and collaborating, please contact Alex Greninger at mailto:agrening@uw.edu.

Comments: The coronavirus sequencing project at JCVI is a collaborative effort with multiple investigators to sequence different alpha and beta coronavirus from human and animals. The specific aims and the scale are different for each study but the broad objectives are to track genomic diversity, virus mutation, adaptation and pathogenesis of coronavirus in humans, and other mammals.
